## What It Does

Galilee Connect keeps your congregation connected through automated daily communications:

- **📖 Daily Bible Verse** — A new verse every morning, delivered to every member
- **🎂 Birthday Wishes** — Personalized birthday greetings on the special day
- **💒 Anniversary Wishes** — Celebrate milestones with your members
- **✉️ Manual Messages** — Send announcements to all or selected members
- **📝 Self-Registration** — Members sign up from their phones

## Quick Start

### 1. Install

```bash
cd galilee-connect
npm install
```

### 2. Configure

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Edit `.env` with your settings:
- **ADMIN_USERNAME** / **ADMIN_PASSWORD** — Dashboard login
- **SMTP settings** — For sending emails (Gmail, SendGrid, etc.)
- **SEND_HOUR** / **SEND_MINUTE** — When daily notifications go out (default: 8:00 AM CST)

### 3. Setup & Seed

```bash
npm run setup
```

This creates the database and adds sample members for testing.

### 4. Run

```bash
npm start
```

Open your browser:
- **Member Registration:** http://localhost:3000
- **Admin Dashboard:** http://localhost:3000/admin

Default admin login:
- Username: `pastor`
- Password: `galilee2024`

## Features

### Admin Dashboard
- View member stats and upcoming birthdays/anniversaries
- Preview and customize daily Bible verse
- Manage notification settings (time, enabled/disabled)
- Send manual messages to all or selected members
- View complete message delivery history

### Member Management
- Add, edit, and remove members
- Import members from CSV files
- Search and filter member list
- Track email and SMS subscriptions

### Notifications
- Automated daily Bible verse (rotates through 100+ curated verses)
- Birthday wishes with customizable templates
- Anniversary wishes with customizable templates
- Manual one-time messages with personalization ({{first_name}}, {{last_name}}, {{full_name}})

### Delivery Channels
- **Email** (via SMTP/Nodemailer) — configured in .env
- **SMS** (via Twilio) — optional, set SMS_ENABLED=true
- Pluggable architecture for future providers (KLT Connect VoIP)

## Email Setup (Gmail)

1. Enable 2-Factor Authentication on your Google account
2. Generate an App Password: Google Account → Security → App Passwords
3. Use these settings in .env:

```
EMAIL_ENABLED=true
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_SECURE=false
SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your-16-char-app-password
```

## SMS Setup (Twilio)

1. Create a Twilio account at https://twilio.com
2. Get your Account SID, Auth Token, and a phone number
3. Add to .env:

```
SMS_ENABLED=true
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=ACxxxxxxxxxx
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=your-auth-token
TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER=+12565551234
```

## CSV Import Format

The CSV importer is flexible and accepts these column names:

```csv
first_name,last_name,email,phone,birthday,anniversary
Mary,Johnson,mary@example.com,(256) 555-0101,03/15,06/20
James,Williams,james@example.com,(256) 555-0102,07-22,
```

Supported date formats: `MM-DD`, `MM/DD`, `MM/DD/YYYY`, `YYYY-MM-DD`

